column5: Damn right that's a big perch!
Damn you get a tape on it?
I'm guessing Rick was nowhere near that fish?

From Wikipedia: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yellow_perch The world record yellow perch (18 in., 4 lb. 3 oz.) was caught in 1865 from New Jersey, and is the longest standing record for freshwater fish in North America.[1] Anglers often refer to large yellow perch as "jumbo perch" or "jack perch".  Looking at that one makes me wonder.
I'm guessing Rick was nowhere near that fish? you know me too well Sir. The link below the photo leads to the proud owner of that fish and the details.
Article states that it is an ice fishing record.  Very impressive regardless
You could feed a family of 4 with 2 of those!  And .... have leftovers!
